The paper discusses the creation of an artificial dataset generator for a high-level task planning domain, which involves the integration of neural and symbolic systems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks and the focus on photo-realistic images suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The mention of systematic and complete algorithms for symbolic reasoning suggests that the paper may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the mention of decomposability into subproblems suggests that the paper may also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category.
